      <div class="product-additional-details-2--col-title">
        <h3 class="h3">What It Is

</h3>
      </div>
    

    
      <div class="product-additional-details-2--col-text">
        <div class="shopify-generated-content text-medium-small-body">
Airset is made of 35% PCR (post-consumer recycled plastic).

</div>

        
      </div>
    
  </li>


                  
                
                  
                    






  <li class="product-additional-details-2--col-block">
    
      <div class="product-additional-details-2--col-title">
        <h3 class="h3">Why we chose it

</h3>
      </div>
    

    
      <div class="product-additional-details-2--col-text">
        <div class="shopify-generated-content text-medium-small-body">
Post Consumer Resin, also known as PCR, is plastic that's been repurposed for use again. Using PCR helps to reduce the amount of new plastic packaging. Products that use PCR drive the demand of the material, which in turn increases its overall use across different industries.

</div>

        
      </div>
    
  </li>


                  
                
                  
                    






  <li class="product-additional-details-2--col-block">
    
      <div class="product-additional-details-2--col-title">
        <h3 class="h3">Recycling

</h3>
      </div>
    

    
      <div class="product-additional-details-2--col-text">
        <div class="shopify-generated-content text-medium-small-body">
Once your Airset jar is empty, remove the sifter and wipe away any remaining product from the jar and sifter. Place the clean sifter, cap and jar in your home recycling bin. 

All of our secondary cartons are made from 100% post-consumer waste and FSC-certified paper. Simply toss the carton in your home recycling bin.

</div>

        
          <div class="cta-block spacing-small">
            <a href="/web/20250428045316/https://saiehello.com/pages/recycling" class="link--cta">Recycle Your Empties</a>
          </div>
        
      </div>
    
  </li>


                  
                
